markets.title: Will a hurricane category 5 hurricane or stronger hit Savannah this year?
markets.subtitle: Category 5 or higher
markets.rules_primary: If the National Weather Service reports that a maximum sustained wind-speed of at least 157 miles per hour (corresponding to a hurricane category  or stronger) in the city of Savannah that occurred between August 11, 2023 and November 30, 2023, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
The Exchange uses two NWS products for its Underlying: (1) the Daily Climate Report for Savannah, Georgia and (2) any location within the city limits of Savannah, Georgia included in an NWS Post-Storm Hurricane Report.

The market will expire on the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of official data at the Underlying confirming the event has occurred. Otherwise, the market will expire on the sooner of the the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of data for November 30, 2023, or one week after November 30, 2023.
